--- !u!114 &212369657
MonoBehaviour:
  m_ObjectHideFlags: 0
  m_CorrespondingSourceObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabInstance: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabAsset: {fileID: 0}
  m_GameObject: {fileID: 212369656}
  m_Enabled: 1
  m_EditorHideFlags: 0
  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: bd8247e9fc96a7f4c95b91b320ab5883, type: 3}
  m_Name: 
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::NpcDialogue
  storyStates:
  - minimumStoryBeat: 0
    location: {fileID: 1464583121}
    isVisible: 1
    isInteractable: 1
    lines:
    - speaker: Pryce
      text: Ah! There you are. Welcome to our little corner of the Helix Facility.
        I'm Director Pryce.
    - speaker: Pryce
      text: I'll keep this brief - your role here is very straightforward.
    - speaker: Pryce
      text: Patrol your routes, check the exits are secure, and most importantly,
        ensure that nothing disrupts the work.
    - speaker: Pryce
      text: The research we do here is important. More important than most people
        will ever understand.
    - speaker: Pryce
      text: ...or even acknowledge...
    - speaker: Pryce
      text: You just need to make sure it continues!
    - speaker: Pryce
      text: The staff here are extremely committed to the work, but that doesn't
        mean you won't find them pleasant. So don't let them distract you from your
        responsibilities.
    - speaker: Pryce
      text: If you have any concerns, come directly to me. Not to the researchers,
        not to the staff. Me.
    - speaker: Pryce
      text: Your route is standard, so you shouldn't have any issues. And the canteen
        is open if you need it.
    - speaker: Pryce
      text: Now, go on. We've already spent far too long yapping about. We've got
        sceince to do.
    storyBeatAfterDialogue: 0
  - minimumStoryBeat: 1
    location: {fileID: 1156857748}
    isVisible: 1
    isInteractable: 1
    lines:
    - speaker: Pryce
      text: Was it the logbook you found?
    - speaker: Cyrus
      text: You knew I would?
    - speaker: Pryce
      text: I did.
    - speaker: Cyrus
      text: So why all the cloak and dagger? The secrecy? If the research is so important,
        why hide it? Why drug an entire facility just to keep them quiet about it?
    - speaker: Pryce
      text: You think the dosage is there to keep them quiet?
    - speaker: Cyrus
      text: Isn't it?
    - speaker: Pryce
      text: 'No, Cyrus. The reset isn''t there to separate them from the research.
        It is the research. '
    - speaker: Pryce
      text: Every batch, every reset, every morning where someone wakes up and doesn't
        remember the day before - thats the data.
    - speaker: Pryce
      text: Years of clean, repeatable cognitive decline, in subjects who never have
        the chance to adapt, or compensate, or resist.
    - speaker: Pryce
      text: 'We''ve learned more about memory and degredation in seven years than
        anyone else has in fifty. '
    - speaker: Cyrus
      text: They never agreed to that!
    - speaker: Pryce
      text: They didn't.
    - speaker: Pryce
      text: You know, you say the same thing every time. "They didn't agree to that."
        And you're always right.
    - speaker: Pryce
      text: Cyrus, you've confronted me more times than I can count. And every time,
        you've stood right where you are now, and decided that the work mattered
        more.
    - speaker: Cyrus
      text: That's not me!
    - speaker: Pryce
      text: It is, actually. It's the only you I've ever known.
    - speaker: Pryce
      text: 'But I''m not going to stop you. I''m not going to ask you to hand anything
        over, or threaten you, or call anyone. '
    - speaker: Pryce
      text: I've tried all of that before. A long time ago. It doesn't change anything.
    - speaker: Pryce
      text: There's the radio if you still want it. And there's your lunch if you
        don't. I'll be here either way. Like always.
    storyBeatAfterDialogue: 1
